# CVE-2025-6985: XXE vulnerability in HTMLSectionSplitter class
# This vulnerability affects the HTMLSectionSplitter class in langchain-text-splitters 0.3.x
# which uses unsafe XSLT parsing. Our codebase only uses RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter,
# not HTMLSectionSplitter, so we are not affected by this vulnerability.
# The only fix is version 1.0.0a1 (alpha), which may have breaking changes.
# Suppressing until a stable 1.0.0 release is available.
# Reference: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-m42m-m8cr-8m58
CVE-2025-6985

# CVE-2026-35030: Authentication bypass in LiteLLM proxy OIDC userinfo cache
# CVE-2026-35029: Remote code execution in LiteLLM proxy configuration
# CVE-2026-42271: Authenticated command execution via LiteLLM MCP stdio test endpoints
# GHSA-69x8-hrgq-fjj8: Password hash exposure in LiteLLM proxy auth
# These CVEs affect LiteLLM proxy/server functionality, which we do not use.
# We use litellm only through LiteLLMEmbeddings, which calls litellm.embedding().
# Fixed LiteLLM versions require httpx>=0.28, while aisuite 0.1.14 still requires
# httpx<0.28. Suppressing until aisuite can resolve with fixed LiteLLM versions.
CVE-2026-35030
CVE-2026-35029
CVE-2026-42271
GHSA-69x8-hrgq-fjj8
